main event: A slightly elliptical, metallic object was observed at Tyndall AFB, Florida on May 9, 1961.
interesting points: The object appeared to be static at first, but then began to move and got smaller, indicating a rapid acceleration.
The object exhibited extensive maneuvering, becoming very small and disappearing on a southwest heading at a 45-degree angle.
The report mentions past reports of aircraft activity and missile firings observed in the area.
Two objects were observed traveling in an oblique formation, with one object traveling southwest to northeast and the other southwest to northwest.
The objects were observed by multiple witnesses, including a civilian, Captain Allan E. Aarenson, and M/Sgt Henry J. Lacour.
witnesses: civilian, Captain Allan E. Aarenson, M/Sgt Henry J. Lacour
